name: Sky Bar, Gran Senyiur Hotel
address: Jln. H ARS. Muhammad 7 Gran Senyiur Hotel, 8th Floor, Balikpapan 76112 Indonesia

reviews.text: Attended sky bar and was thoroughly impressed with the atmosphere, Decor and service. The food was excellent, especially the variety of seafood and the grilled prawns in particular were large as exceptionally tasty. The view was very good and the band complimented the atmosphere nicely
reviews.title: Solid view very good food

reviews.text:
the place is located in the gran senyiur's roof top. from lobby area, they provide a dedicated lift to access the place.

they served all round menu. they have both indoor and outdoor seating. for a better view, outdoor seating is recommended, although it can be so windy.

the price is moderately high, as it is a 5star hotel.

the food was just ok. the place is suitable to chat with friends or colleague, but not more than that.
reviews.title: good view, ordinary food

reviews.text: Beautiful view from the terrace of the bar. It is a very pleasant place to spend some time in the evening.
reviews.title: Nice view

reviews.text: very beautiful  and romantic night view. Food is okay, reasonable price. I don't mind to come back again
reviews.title: perfect for a date night

reviews.text: Came here last night. Nice view and upmarket though abit dated. Ordered the premium beef burger which was ok for the standard. My wie ordered a vermicelli salad. Its was sooo spicy it was unedible and she has a high chilli tolerance. The sauce seemed to be chilli vinegar!
reviews.title: Nice view . Ok food can be hit and miss

reviews.text: Very expensive and the food is mediocre! The view is good but much of Balikpapan is being developed so... Not recommended.
reviews.title: Sky bar

reviews.text: Probably, u should try this kind of sky bar and resto , u can see night city view from here especially most beautiful at night. Spend ur chill time in here could be worth it, nice foods but not for the staff, waitress doesn't show hospitality i forgot her name.
reviews.title: Great nightcity view

reviews.text:
Not recommended, not all the foods available especially desserts, the waitress wasnt really nice maybe because we came really late that night. But please, not kind at all. 
The view was nice though.
reviews.title: Not recommended

reviews.text: Not at all recommended. Ordered steamboat for 234k and guessed what you have: 2 stripes of local beef, mie telor, low quality sausage.
reviews.title: Mr

reviews.text: The place is quite posh. Pricey but you are paying for the view as well. Service is good but there are lots of mosquito in the veranda.
reviews.title: Chillin' with a view

reviews.text:
Nice view sky scrapper, warm and friendly ambience, can be a romantic place for dinner.

Shall go back to try some of the other signature dishes first.
reviews.title: View Dining

reviews.text:
It has many options for indonesian and western food.
the price was reasonable considering the superb location.
reviews.title: good food with amazing view

reviews.text: located on top of the hotel the bar offers a nice view on the city of Balikapan and the ocean. It is certainly pricier than other places but worth a visit, especially since it is not overcrowded and offers a good service.
reviews.title: roof top bar with a view

reviews.text: If you are in the vicinity of this, you must go for a sunset drink. Its mandatory. The 8th floor views are fantastic, overlooking the coast of Balikpapan, the large mosque and new Botany Bay Shopping Mall, still under construction. The drinks were affordable although hotel prices, but were well worth it. We missed the sunset, but the views were still great.
reviews.title: Great views, with apparently stunning sunsets!

reviews.text: The first and only sky bar in Balikpapan. The view, especially, during the night is very beautiful, since the hotel located in the center of the city. They served western menu here.
reviews.title: Beautiful view at night

reviews.text: Open top seafood restaurant, prawns, crab, fish, rice and wine, the food was speedily served and was of good fresh quality. Service was good, enjoyed the whole experience.
reviews.title: Evening meal

reviews.text:
Amazing city seeing view. Nice liquor, food, bbq and very helpful staff.
Avoid to visit at rainy day or you couldn't see anything.
reviews.title: Amazing top view

reviews.text: great view, great staff , great for small kids with a really nice play ground for the kids,Gran Senyiur Hotal is is old school but very nice
reviews.title: Sky Bar

reviews.text: Place is very good but food choice is limited, open upto 12:00 morning but you may not get your food choice after 11:00 PM
reviews.title: Bar in sky!!! feeling high ,,,,

reviews.text:
You go there for the view (most likely the best in town) and the drinks go nicely with it.
The cocktails are quite okay (do not ask for the difference between Margarita and Frozen Margarita, they would not know) and you get a big load of peanuts and chips with it.
Service is helpful and friendly
It is a nice way to finish up a day in Balikpapan
reviews.title: The view is fantastic and even some cocktails are

name: Open House
address: Kelurahan Damai Jln. Puncak Marconi Indah 88, Balikpapan 76114 Indonesia

reviews.text: I can only say, please add vegetarian options to the menu, as we struggled and only ate wedges. But easily one of the most beautiful place to eat in Balikpapan, and staff were very friendly and attentive.
reviews.title: Gorgeous place, but not great for vegetarians

reviews.text:
Make sure to check the dates in previous reviews. Open house is a beautiful location, but none of the reviews were accurate. There is no international or Mediterranean cuisine, there is a medium sized selection of Indonesian food, mostly snacks. They advertise as vegetarian friendly, but the staff (who were very kind and helpful) struggled to identify vegetarian options. The food was not great. They dont take credit card, so make sure you bring cash. No alcohol/beer.

There are tables for literally hundreds of people and we were the only ones in the restaurant section. Im sure this will pick up after COVID, but for now it is very sparse. Interesting place with lots of potential.
reviews.title: Check updated reviews! A lot of changes.

reviews.text:
restaurant is really beautiful with phantastic view. negative is the quality of food. was really not good, and for indonesia expensiv. we eat mixed, meat, fish etc. but all the food was really poor quality. after we left we went to place we know to eat again. at the end....
.for a drink and nice view is worth at any time.....for dinner go somewhere else
reviews.title: nice view

reviews.text:
Had a quick stop in the afternoon on my recent visit to Balikpapan.

Balikpapan is a wonderful city bustling with Metro like atmosphere at the gate of East Kalimantan .. a unique destination with many challenging eco attractions ...

I was lucky enough to sit down at Open House Balikpapan right on sunset when all the colours come alive .. was quite an experience .. food and bevs are quite good with friendly service ..

Will certainly revisit on the next trip. And maybe great to stay at Hilltop House next door as well ..
reviews.title: Amazing Balikpapan City View

reviews.text: Nice place to hangout with friends, it is on top of a hill so we can see Balikpapan from top but food is overprice and taste so average.
reviews.title: Nah

reviews.text: The place was very interesting. They had more outdoor space than any other restaurants we had visited in Balikpapan. We had to walk through quite beautiful scenary to get to the restaurant from the parking lot. We sit outdoor (thank God it wasn't rainning) and it was chilly and windy but it was nice for a change. We ordered Lamb Souvlaki which was good and quite the right amount to fill our stomach. The prices were a bit expensive though.
reviews.title: Interesting place

reviews.text:
I've been to Open House several times over the last couple of years and the view never fails to impress!  I recommend visiting just before sunset so that you can see the view over the city and out to see, which is beautiful.

There layout and decor of the restaurant are really interesting and it's well worth taking the time to explore during your visit - finding swimming pools, art work, some antiques, and all mixed with an exotic fusion of East meets West.  

The downside to Open House, in my opinion, is the unpredictable food. Sometimes it's really lovely (the vegetarian platter is fabulous!), but sometimes it's just OK, which is disappointing because it's all relatively expensive.  Also, too often various menu items are not available.

I definitely think Open House is worth a visit, but maybe it would be worth contacting the restaurant first to make sure they know you're going.
reviews.title: Come for the view...

photos.caption: Looking from an upper level to a middle level.
From the top floor, looking towards the ocean.

reviews.text: the rooms where not as I expected. It looked old and it wasn't the best quality at all for that price. I expected more. For food the restaurant area is great. But for a nights stay over it's just mediocre.
reviews.title: The view was perfect but...

reviews.text:
Beautiful place with Balinese decorations infinity view Balikpapan oil city, romantic place for couples, variance food and beverage was over with huge parking area
Recommended for tourist's
reviews.title: Infinite view

reviews.text:
We have been here a few times, in recent month the prices are very high for Balikpapan or even in Asia. Chicken meat only Kebab with a few frozen chips and a greasy awful looking salad cost is RP160,000 plus 21% for taxes and service. 
Staff not helpful, they never asked if the food is okay, nor did they ask if we wanted anything else. We had to keep getting up to ask for assistance with ordering, asking for the bill etc. Views are good but can't see the Sunset. Wouldn't go back sorry.
reviews.title: It was okay, great views

reviews.text:
We spent 3 nights in the eco room, the hotel itself is absolutely stunning with amazing views of Balikpapan. 
Only real issue was no hot water available in the shower and our room did smell a little moldy. 
The restaurant has quite good food but was often out of certain dishes and is quite expensive comparatively. 
Otherwise it was on of the most beautiful hotels I've ever been in,  definitely recommended
reviews.title: Beautiful beautiful hotel

reviews.text: The view is very nice, and its like secluded, it felt like i was somewhere else outside the city. But the food is expensive and i ordered the chef recommended food but sadly didn't get it because one of the materials was not available. Taste of the food was good.
reviews.title: Beautiful view, pricey food

reviews.text: Medierranean food and try also the local cusine,its one of the finest resto of Balikpapan, open house has an unique setting,has a pagoda tower style,looking to Balikpapan bay..what a great view...
reviews.title: Architecture art

reviews.text: Food is good but worth going just for the setting. Lovely gardens and great view of the city. Staff were friendly and efficient. Meals were tasty and good value for the price. Ask to sit up the top for the best views.
reviews.title: Lovely setting

reviews.text: I like the food esp. Ikan bakar and masi goreng. We can the view of balikpapan from our table. The place is cozy and unique
reviews.title: Dinner at open house

reviews.text: I was the only person in the restaurant when I visited here - maybe because it was a Tuesday night.. Food is ok, the portions are small, but probably normal size for balikpapan & service was a little slow. It is just out of the city centre, but on hillside, so would get some nice views in the daytime. Got the feeling it is a romantic venue as my taxi driver on way home was a little surprised I was there alone...
reviews.title: Flying solo meal..

reviews.text: Foods n drinks are overpriced, but view from this resto is amazing, especially in the night.. If you ever come to Bandung,  this resto just looks like resto in Dago Hill area..
reviews.title: Overpriced, but amazing view

reviews.text:
The food not delicious, not much variety, and bored.
The place is very cozy and have a great great city view.
If you visit this place to take selfie  will be better than trying the food.
reviews.title: Two times and always dissapointed

reviews.text: This place is wonderful. the restaurant is build on different levels. each level has is own design. I really love the place but.... The food is far from expectations and the prices are very high compare to the quality. No alcohol but you can bring yours.

reviews.text: Located in Puncak Markoni, Food is average taste, but we could get good panorama and get your dine or lunch with nice sea & city view.

crunchy....the egg crab is good,

reviews.text:
Good food with good service, staffs were courteous and polite. Food was fast and delicious, live up to the name.

I had crab with dandito's sauce and it is recommended. Grilled squid was also delicious.
reviews.title: Don't forget to booked in advance if you want to bring famous crab menu home

reviews.text: Totally delicious crab dishes, love the sauce especially black pepper sauce, famous culinary in Balikpapan, it's a must visited for all culinary enthusiasts
reviews.title: Five star crab dish

reviews.text:
The most recommended restaurant for enjoying crab. I always order the male crab as it has more meat. Try saos padang or black pepper crabs. 

The ambience is more into a traditional restaurant. There is live music at night.
reviews.title: Must try crab

reviews.text:
Nice place for eating crab and other fresh seafood nearly Balikpapan Airports. This is one of our family favorites seafood restaurant the taste of dishes are fresh and nice better than other.
If you want to eat in group I suggest to make reservations before
reviews.title: Crab Lovers place in Balikpapan

reviews.text: Dont forget to visit this place when you go to balikpapan and looking crabs and seafood. You can bring to your home with package request when you dont have time to stay a long.

reviews.text: we visited this restaurant during lunch time. good and quick service. the crab at this restaurant is a must try dish. i will come back and visit again in the future.

reviews.text: A great restaurant for crab lovers,as Balikpapan is surrounded with shrimp and crab farms, the soft shelled crab and the mud crabs are a must have at this restaurant,

reviews.text: the best spicy crab ever. the price may be slightly expensive than other, but you will not be disappointed. They provide a packaging box that secure for taking away even in the airplane baggage.

name: Bondy Restaurant
address: Jl. Jenderal Ahmad Yani No. 1 Klandasan Ilir, Balikpapan 76113 Indonesia

reviews.text: Great food and fresh fish you can definately have, tasty, the vibe... the atmosphere of the restaurant ... a very well known
reviews.title: A very well known restaurant you must visit and eat!

reviews.text: Since I was younger, this restaurant was one of the restaurants we would visit at least once a month. My family, including my cousins and my grandparents, would eat lunch here after church or for a birthday party of our family members. The food here was great and we enjoyed it very much, a negative point for me though is their restroom. It wasn't the most comfortable restroom to use. Either way still very recommended to eat with your small and large families, they give a wide variety of dishes everyone can enjoy! After the pandemic happen we visit way less, but nonetheless still an enjoyable restaurant.
reviews.title: A Monthly Visit

reviews.text:
Bondy's has always been a favourite dining place for us whenever we visit Balikpapan and its been 2 years since our last visit and this time was just as enjoyable as all our previous visits.
Great variety of seafoods and different methods of preperation are always enjoyable.
Highly reccommend this place for anyone visiting Balikpapan.
reviews.title: Dinner with my wife before we fly out of Balikpapan

reviews.text:
We were taken here for a business lunch. Its a small restaurant with predominantly fish menu, but also has an adjacent bakery. 

All apart from me opted for fish which looked very good. I had a taste of the fish myself and it was nice and not too spicy. I opted for the Persian kebab with fries and that was equally as delicious as the fish. Complimentary soup is also served. They joined two tables together which was able to seat 9. Waitress was attentive and it was an excellent lunch. I would never have found it had our hosts not taken us there.
reviews.title: Authentic local fish restaurant

reviews.text: Bondy Restaurant is famous with their signature seafood dishes, and sometimes we ordered for take away. But in this visit, we tried for their signature burgers and ice cream. The Burger just like a real American burgers, with a very meaty patty, soft bun and fresh garnish. Their ice cream also the best in  town. The ambience is very quaint, a littlw crewpy though, but it was reasonable as it is an old classic restaurant. Didnt take picts coz we're busy with kids. Staffs are friendly and lwt our kids run around safely.
reviews.title: classic high class restaurant

reviews.text:
Almost completely Restaurant with Beef or Chicken Steak and seafood menu.
Suitable for couple, family & business Lunch or Dinner.
Spacey dine areas and delicious main courses and desserts.
reviews.title: Old Chinese Restaurant with special menu of Steak & Seafoods

reviews.text:
Really love the crab at this resto

Fishes are fress and all food here delicious 
Really bad i just have video

reviews.title: Dinner with family

This restaurant have home made ice cream that become a legend in balikpapan, and i took my time to try for it.

Been here several times now. The food is great and reasonably priced for seafood
 Good service and environment too
reviews.title: Seafood dinner

reviews.text: The food's taste is okay. The place is clean and spacy too. But i don't like this place arrangement. It's a bakery shop in front part of this place. We eat in the inner part of this place

reviews.text: Has been one of the most consistent seafood restaurants in Balikpapan. I first visited Bondy's back in 1996 when I first visited Indonesia for work and the quality has been pretty consistent even to my last visit last year when we left Balikpapan.
reviews.title: Business dinner with a work colleague from Chille.

reviews.text: so far, the food was good, the view so nice. The parking area is small. But hey boss can u train ur staff to smile?
reviews.title: nice food, but smile a lil bit please !!

reviews.text:
We went to Bondy for my mothers birthday.  When we arrived all the wait staff just stared at us from a distance while we found our own table. The waitress (Ana) was very rude and arrogant.  She proceeded to forget one of our drinks (not a big deal).  

When we ordered she didn't know the prices of some items on the menu.  Then when we actually ordered, the food took around 20 mins (not bad).  

But my husbands meal didn't arrive so we asked the waitress.  She told us it takes a long time and left.  10 minutes later we asked a waiter, he said he would go check and never came back.  It was now 45 mins after we had ordered so we said that it the meal didn't arrive in the next 5 mins, we wouldn't pay for it.  At this point they told us they had never actually placed that order.

At the end of the meal we asked to take away some left overs, the arrogant waitress told us to 'just wait' as she had other customers.  She never came back.

When we were paying we asked to speak to a manager.  They dont have a manager.

We asked to make a complaint. They dont have a process for that.

I asked for a postal address of the restaurant and the name of someone who is actually in charge.  Not possible.

We will not be going back.
reviews.title: Terrible service and average food

reviews.text: Must try! You can skip other meals on the menu but make sure try this one. The pepes patin is very juicy and tasty
reviews.title: Best pepes patin in the world

reviews.text:
They serve a lot of options! Seafood, vegan, steak, bakery, you name it. It is pretty similar with Gandy restaurant in Jakarta with extra seafood. Not a child friendly place. Again most seafood restaurant here does not cater for kids, except if you order fried fish and eat them with soya sauce. Period. 

They cater for big groups. Offer vallet service since the parking space is so minimal. Service is fast. Compare to other seafood restaurant in Balikpapan. Price is reasonable, i guess thats why our secretary and boss love it there.
reviews.title: Only visited it with office friends - for special occasions

reviews.text: This restaurant has been established for as long as i can remember. Never failed to satisfy me. The food was amazing, especially sea food, grilled fish and shrimp, lobster, and etc, all is superb. This resto also has many different area to dine in, indoor and outdoor. I prefer outdoor. I feel more comfortable, beautiful place to dine surrounded by flowers and small trees. Excellent restaurant.
reviews.title: Balikpapan heritage

name: Soto Banjar Kuin Abdhu
address: Jl. Jenderal Ahmad Yani No. 01 Gunungsari Ilir, Balikpapan 76113 Indonesia

reviews.text: More than once a time I come here and mostly with my clients as I am a tour guide and need to share the experience of how the local food is. Well, my clients love it as I do. One thing to improve is the place as it's always crowded so it needs space bigger.
reviews.title: Good food

reviews.text: I tried the branch, a traditional waroong with tasty soto. The best Banjar Soto in Balikpapan. The chicken satay however is average. The ambience is simple seating and traditional style waroong.
reviews.title: The best Banjar Soto in Balikpapan

reviews.text:
Its another variety of Indonesia's Soto. The brorth is very light, tasty. They served with rice or rice cake. The most interesting is they put casava to make the broth thick..
Price is affordable. 

Love to come back again
reviews.title: Light and very tasty Soto!

reviews.text: We had good memories of this resto back 5 years ago...at that time, the taste was good and all of us love to eat Yummy Soto Banjar...but now the quality is poor...even to eat half is effortful
reviews.title: Please improve the quality of foods

reviews.text: The Banjar Soup is so delicious, if you want to try eat someting with spicy and traditional recipes you should try this Banjar Soup
reviews.title: Nice Banjar Soup in Balikpapan

reviews.text:
I categorized this as street food. Small store in the busy street and no aircon..so prepare to sweat a bit.
Its simple, unique but truly delicious, two thumbs up. No need to ad too much things in the soto soup. Just a squeeze of lime. The soto is already a bit spicy.
Unique bcs it has duck egg and casava inside..but again perfect combination.
The chicken sate is okay...
You can have the soto with rice or rice cake...
reviews.title: Excellent street food

reviews.text:
My favourite soto banjar in Balikpapan. It's not a fancy restaurant, but the food taste is awesome. 

Combine soto banjar with chicken satay. They have authentique flavour that makes you go back and forth here.
reviews.title: Favourite soto banjar in Balikpapan

reviews.text: I was looking for Queen Sidewalk eatery and was greeted with KUIN instead. A dish of Chicken Soto and Satay awaits. The Hot Soto was well seasoned, filled with thick chiken chunks and tasty sliced boiled duck egg...very good to clear up your throat. The satay is served with delicious coarse peanut sauce. A nite treat I dont mind doing again once back in town
reviews.title: Refreshing supper

reviews.text: The chicken satay was great, it tasted so delicious with it sauce. The soto (I don't know its name in english) was refreshing and made you want some more...
reviews.title: Delightful...

reviews.text:
Nice soto, with great taste. Quite unique, with chicken satay and perkedel.
Reasonable price also.......................
reviews.title: Delicious

reviews.text: It's a small but clean warung just at the side of the street. The soto is fresh and tasty (balanced, not too salty). A very recommended place if you bored with the seafood restaurant ;) I also love the ice tea, it has a hint of vanilla flavour. Ps. Beware of the sambal though... Very very spicy :p

reviews.text: The soto is great, but the satay is the best. The satay covered with almost similar with padang sauce. The taste is great and it is an Indonesian authentic food
reviews.title: Great authentic satay

reviews.text:
This Soto Banjar tasted nice on every condiment and dressing, little big portion for diet woman like me, hehe, but overall is very nice

You may order the soto separate from rice or lontong and don't forget to order its satay too, yummy, almost flawless

But for car parking area little bit difficult
reviews.title: What a tasty Soto banjar

reviews.text:
soto banjar bisa menjadi alternatif klo mulai bingung mau makan apa di balikpapan. yang terkenal adalah soto banjar kuin abdhu di kawasan gunung sari.

harga bersahabat 20ribuan/porsi. pesan satenya sekalian biar makin mantapp
reviews.title: alternatif makanan

reviews.text: Untuk pertama kalinya mencoba soto banjar, dan soto banjar Kuin Abdhu di jalan Ahamad Yani ini memang enak. Harga sangat bersahabat. 1 porsi soto dengan kupat setengah hanya Rp. 16.000. Very recommended!

reviews.text: tempat makannya terbilang sederhana dan kira-kira hanya dapat menampung 40-50 pengunjunh dan selalu ramai. seporsi soto banjar dilengkapi dengan perkedel singkong, suiran daging ayam kampung, telur bebek dan soun serta taburan bawang goreng dan daun seledri
reviews.title: makan soto banjar

reviews.text:
Ini soto ? Bukan, kan ga pake ketupat
Ini sop ? Bukan,  kan ga pake nasi
Trus ini apa ? Sop aja ... pake perkedel segede gaban
reviews.title: sop atau soto

reviews.text:
Berkunjung ke kota Balikpapan, tidak akan lengkap bila belum mencicipi salah satu kuliner andalan khas kota ini, yaitu Soto Banjar. Dan salah satu warung soto legendaris yang sudah sering saya dengar dari berbagai teman dan kolega adalah warung Soto Banjar Kuin Adhu ini. 
Warung Soto Banjar ini memang salah satu warung yang legendaris, eksistensinya sudah lama banget dan sangat dikenal di kalangan masyarakat Balikpapan. Pelanggannya sangat banyak, bukan hanya masyarakat setempat tetapi juga dari berbagai kota lain, termasuk wisatawan dan pengunjung kota Balikpapan dari Jakarta dan kota-kota besar lainnya.
Wajar bila warung soto ini menjadi salah satu tujuan wisata kuliner di kota ini. Karena cita rasanya memang sudah tidak perlu diragukan lagi. Kuah sotonya begitu harum dengan aroma aneka bumbu dan rempah andalan yang menjadi rahasia sekaligus kunci rasa sotonya. Kuahnya berwana kuning sedikit kental, dengan aroma santan yang lembut. 
Dalam semangkok soto banjar ini, potongan dagingnya cukup banyak dan tidak pelit. Dagingnya empuk dan langsung lumer saat digigit di mulut. Dengan cita rasa yang sangat nikmat itu, harga yang dipatok menjadi tidak terasa mahal.
reviews.title: Soto Banjar Wajib Dicicipi

reviews.text:
(+) soto dan sate enak. Layanan cepat. Harga terjangkau

(-) parkir susah. Topping sotonya kurang banyak (ayam, soun, perkedel kentang)
reviews.title: Soto dan Satenya Mantap!

name: Ocean's
address: Jln. Jendral Sudirman Komplek Rukan Bandar Balikpapan Blok M 18, Balikpapan 76112 Indonesia

reviews.text:
Ocean's restaurant opens at 10.00 am, is a seafood restaurant with a location on the seafront. The location is safe because it will not be hit by a tsunami in East Kalimantan. The view from the ocean restaurant will be very beautiful in the afternoon because there are cozy vibes, the beach, and the sunset. This beach is known as the menara beach.
Their kite option is eaten in, take away but they don't provide delivery service. The food there is very good, the seafood served is also varied, ranging from fish, crabs, to shrimp. Prices offered for various seafood menus start from 75,000 to hundreds of thousands. I have a recommendation for a delicious food menu there, namely crab, lobster, and fish kerapu, I hope I hadn't eaten so much because it's addictive. In addition to providing a place or outdoor space they also have a closed room or room, inside there is live music too. However, unfortunately, the location for parking vehicles is quite difficult or not wide enough because it joins the surrounding shops. Although the parking area isn't spacious, there are still many customers who keep eating there and visiting. I went there after I had leisured time.
reviews.title: seaside romance

reviews.text: Good food with sea view worth with the price. Mostly people come for talking bussiness not only for dinner.

name: Kepiting Kenari
address: Jalan Iswahyudi no.4, Balikpapan Indonesia

reviews.text:
This restaurant is a must when you visit Balikpapan, the location near the airport that you can easily visit when you've arrived here. This restaurant provides pretty good facilities which are nothing to worry about that they have really big space to accommodate people. They provide many kinds of seafood such as crab, shrimp, squid, and scallop starts from 261k you can get 1 portion of sauce crab with an optional sauce of your choice (black pepper, Padang sauce, oyster sauce, and sweet & sour sauce) since the crab is one of the famous seafood in Balikpapan. This restaurant also provides you another menu, chicken and also meat which will provide other options for you.
Even though the place is a little bit far away from town, they will always be crowded. This is my absolute favorite seafood restaurant in Balikpapan, the food is always fantastic, and no matter what I order I am always delighted with the meal they served me!
reviews.title: Great restaurant with delicious menu

reviews.text: A restaurant that specialises in seafood and more specifically crab. Crab is available prepared in multiple different ways (black pepper, sweet/sour, etc). Large portions on the crab, less so on the veggies. No alcohol served here.

Disappointing...should try other newly open crab resto.

reviews.text:

Went here after trying other places. Not easy to look for good eateries in Balikpapan, most of them are overpriced with mediocre taste. Torani was really good, with the right price. My friend and I ordered the grilled milk fish, crispy fried milk fish, stir fried squid and crab soup. Everything came about 15 minutes after we ordered. The rice, sambal/chilli and vegetables are self service, you take as much as you can finish.
Easily would recommend this place.

reviews.text: Best and, they said, the pioneer of boneless grilled milk-fish in Balikpapan. No wonder this place is always full of customer even though the place is so big. Rice and soup are served free, yet the taste is so good. There are several chilly sauces you can pick. The price is quite cheap for Balikpapan benchmark.

name: Depot Simpang Empat
address: Jln. Jendral Sudirman Markoni, Sesudah Bakso & Mie Ayam Likmin, Balikpapan 76114 Indonesia

reviews.text:
Each people have a place or activity where they can find joy and tranquility. Whenever I feel blue, eating always gives me pleasure. Food always makes me better and happier; they are sunshine and medicine for my soul. The aroma of food lightens me up, the savoury or sweetness makes my heart fills with satisfaction.
Ive eaten at most Chinese restaurants in Balikpapan over the years. But Depot Simpang Empat, which is my absolute favorite restaurant. Despite the location is very far from my house, I had been to Depot Simpang Empat several times, it just never gets old. The menu, where it offers a wide variety of appetizing traditional Chinese food. Every time I went there, I always try different dishes and I had tried most of individual dish, it serves a special authentic taste. 
Even though the place is a bit old and wonky, but I dont mind it. The restaurant gives the opportunity to seek the culture of Chinese food. People who eat here came for a unique experience that they never feel, and in here, they do get it. To sum up, if you want to experience authentic Chinese foods, I recommend you try Depot Simpang Empat.

reviews.text:

owner_response.text:
Dear Yannick B, 

Thank you for taking the time to review your experience at Garden Restaurant. I read your remarks with great concern and I appreciate your sharing it directly with us. and I would like to assure you that this is not our usual standard.
Kindly accept my sincere apologies for the things that happened. Your feedback will be shared with the entire team to avoid similar cases in the future and to ensure our services to the highest standards for valued guests such as you.

We hope we will have a new chance to welcome you back to Garden Restaurant.



Warm Regards, 


Eko Widhi
F&B Manager
owner_response.title: Owner Response

reviews.text:
There's a great vibe in the place: probably down to the very business clientele. , levels of formality and fashion. It's also frequented by a healthy Indonesian crowd suggesting this isn't just a tourist trap. There was western, traditional ( oxtail soup ) soo yummy dishes.

As a result it's a place you want to stay.. for hours.  it'll be successful because you'll enjoy yourself. If it's friends you'll have a great conversation. If it's a business dinner you'll do the deal. That kind of place. 

The decor is good something missing, but i don't know what ?, amplified by the lighting.the use of sofas and larger chairs makes you feel like you've got your own space. 

Service is top notch. Highly attentive and very very quick. 

The food,, not many choices, and im lucky get oxtail soup. i heard french chef on board from the staff, hope the chef could give something interesting and creative in their menu. 
this restaurant should be on the list for business trip. You won't regret it.
reviews.title: Good Food and Friendly services

reviews.text: Staff is totally good and friendly. I think the ceiling fans in the outdoor area are rotating the wrong way. It's always so hot out there so we often go to Coffee Bean because it's much cooler.

reviews.text:
The baristas and servers at Starbucks eWalk BSB are the most friendly staff in town! They always smile brightly and say "hello" and call you by name whenever you walk into the store.

However, sometimes there are problems at the store, but those problems usually seem to be a fault with whoever is responsible for ordering supplies for the store.  One time, there was no coffee.  (No coffee at Starbucks??!!??!!)  Another time (very recently) there were only Venti size drinks available - no Tall or Grande cups.  And one day there were no sugar sachets available.

There are plenty of tables to sit at, and some comfy couches, and the place is always clean and tidy.

But it's always the serving staff who make Starbucks eWalk enjoyable.
reviews.title: Most Friendly Baristas in Balikpapan!

The food is also good; fried fish, calamari etc but as predicted: pricey.
The parking lot is also used for people visiting monument next to it, so sometimes it's full but not the restaurant.

reviews.text: We knew this place from our friend because it seems the place that always recommended is Ocean. But , truly, for me , this place is better and meet my expectations. reviews.text:
I was planning to have lunch with friends.
So when we arrived, we ask for AC room.
The waiter said that there is 50k/hour charges if below 10 persons. There was no terms like that before. So we go and ask the manager. Surprisingly he said it is 100k/hour.
All my life never met a restaurant like this.
It is okay if restaurant have minimum charges, but charges per hour? Are we karaoke or something?
So we took off and go somewhere else.
Not gonna eat here again ever
reviews.title: Worst services ever

reviews.text:
Restoran yg terletak dikota balikpapan ini menawarkan beragam menu olahan sea food.

Beberapa jenis ikan seperti trakulu, kakap, baronang, bawal, sampai kerapu, udang, kepiting, cumi bahkan gurame dan udang galah yang bukan "sea" pun siap dipilih langsung untuk diolah menjadi makanan yang enak

Tempat makan yang nyaman untuk suasana santai, dan untuk yang buru2 sebaiknya pesan menu terlebih dahulu sehingga ga akan terlalu lama menunggu. Tapi meskipun menunggu ga bakal bosen ko, karna bisa menikmati suasana tepi pantai lengkap dengan anginnya, dan terkadang di malam hari ada live musicnya.

Ada 2 tempat yang disediakan disini, indoor yang dilengkapi AC, dan outdoor yang lengkap juga dengan AG alias "angin geugeuleubugan" karna kencangnya angin laut. untuk yang indoor selain bangunanya terletak di gedung utama restoran, ada juga yang bentuknya seperti gazebo, yang tentunya full AC, sedangkan untuk yang outdoor terdapat 3 tempat pilihan ada di teras belakang restoran yang ada canopy nya, ada di gazebo, dan ada juga di ruang terbuka beratapkan langit.
reviews.title: Makan enak

reviews.text: Ini adalah restoran khas menu sea food. Lokasinya strategis di pusat kota Balikpapan. Area makan sangat luas baik dibagian depan, tengah maupun belakang yang langsung berada dibibir pantai. Petugas restoran siaga didepan lobby untuk mengarahkan pengunjung. Ada spot-spot menarik untuk berfoto. Menunya lezat khas makanan laut.

reviews.text:
We go to De Cafe Resto about two times per month for a business lunch.  This restaurant has been around for as long as I can remember 20 or more years.  And the facilities are starting to look very aged and unpleasant.  Today there was 12 staff in our area however non of them that were supposed to be monitoring the customers where even looking at us.  Every time we needed something we had to yell to one of them to get their attention.  The staff seems to change all the time and they are not very good.  we asked that our starters come first and mains come second.  if not they would have certainly been out of order.  OK the starters did come first and the mains came about four minutes later.  hmmm ?  So while we tried to finisher our starters the mains became cool. It seems to be a universal problem here in Indonesia for restaurant staff to understand how to time the food delivery.  Inside the restaurant looks dirty.  I wonder how the kitchen looks? Also a lot of items on the menu were not available.  We business lunch everyday so we'll probably but De Cafe Resto at the bottom of our list to return to.
James.
reviews.title: De Cafe Resto - needs a reset!

reviews.text: all the menus spoil our tongues. special for the break fast menu De cafe has a corner takjil providing various entrees. De cafe must be on the Must place to come if  you visit to Balikpapan with beef chili pepper plus mantaw and crispy teriyaki salmon became the most favorite menu. Everything is delicious fron maincourse to pastry event the kinds of drinks. My favorite drinks is golden squash ( kiam boi and honey mix with sparkling water )

I came here for an afternoon tea. It is located across the main street from Novetel hotel, of which where I stayed. There is another Bakery (Holland) next door but it doesn't have eat-in sitting.

De caf does not carry many choices of pastry or cakes as in Holland Bakery, but the dine in area is lovely decorated with nice lighting.  I ordered a cup of caf latte and a piece of strawberry cake, the best I could choose among few options. The cake wasn't too dry, in view there is little turnover in this Indonesian city.

It is a nice place to sit around in a cool environment during the sunny afternoon.
reviews.title: Lovely ambience for afternoon tea in Balikpapan city

reviews.text: Siamo capitati in questo ristorante perch ospiti del Blue Sky Hotel. Pesce molto fresco, addirittura presente in vasche con possibilit di sceglierlo personalmente. Ho preso dei calamari cucinati in 3 modi diversi (fritti, grigliati e con salsa al pepe) tutti davvero buonissimi; il mio compagno invece ha preso laragosta e ha detto che era ottima! Prezzo sicuramente alto per lIndonesia, ovviamente per noi italiani invece vantaggioso; abbiamo speso 30 a testa per aragosta e calamari in quantit industriale con birra e acqua. Super consigliato!
reviews.title: Ottimo!

reviews.text: Resto ini tempatnya nyaman dengan desain interior yang menawan. Penataannya baik dan serasi. Layanannya ramah serta memuaskan. Tersedia menu seperti Salad, Kepiting lada hitam, Sapi lada hitam, Udang saus telor asin, Kerapu steam, Sayur paku, Ikan bakar rica rica dan sebagainya. Saladnya terasa segar dan nikmat. Sapi lada hitam rasanya enak dengan bumbu yang nikmat serta daging yang empuk. Udang saus telor asin rasanya enak dan gurih.
reviews.title: Menikmati Makanan di Tempat Menawan

reviews.text: Mepet waktu dengan jadwal pesawat tidak sempat membawa oleh2 kepiting khas Balikpapan, di bandara saya membeli Kepiting Blue Sky, harga hampir sama dengan yang di luar Bandara. Ketika saya dengan pasangan mencoba ... ternyata enak sekali.
reviews.title: ... kurang direkomen utk oleh2 tapi ternyata enak :-)

locations.name: Island Seafood Terrace - Blue Sky Hotel

reviews.text: Suasananya nyaman, tenang.. makanannya enak, harus cobain drh ikan bakar rica rica nya dan kepitting telur asin
reviews.title: Dinner

reviews.text: Saya memesan makan di restaurant ini, karena saya sedang stay di bluesky hotel. Masakan yang variatif dan cita rasa yang menyenangkan, saya memesan kepeting telur asin, udang goreng, toge, dan sayuran, untuk kualitas penyajian standard hotel, dan harga sesuai dengan restaurant tersebut.
reviews.title: Sajian seafood hotel yang enak

reviews.text: Untuk rasa nya sudah tidak diragukan lagi. Menu rekomendasi saya adalah Kepiting saus Telur Asin. Saya sudah mencoba dibeberapa tempat yang menyajikan menu kepiting, dan Islan Seafood Restaurant ini lah  yang paling enak. Udang gandum nya pun ngga kalah enaknya. Pokoknya buat penggemar seafood, wajib nyobaiin ini. Mereka juga buka counter di Bandara Balikpapan, jadi bisa dibawa ke luar kota...
reviews.title: Ngga diragukan lagi...

name: RM Tahu Sumedang Samboja
address: Jl. Sukarno Hatta KM 50 - 52 Kecamatan Samboja Kutai Kartanegara, Balikpapan Indonesia

reviews.text: This restaurant serve sundanesse food. You should try tahu sumedang, tahu pedas and ketoprak. I love tahu pedas, spicy and full of vegetable. Nice place to take a rest when you drive to Samarinda from Balikpapan and it's easy to find.
reviews.title: Tahu Sumedang

reviews.text: Best.. best and best tahu sumedang.. they also serves another sundanesse food, even worth just to spend lunch here from balikpapan.. and also the taste of its tahu sumedang is original.. and it have to big restaurant opposite one another..
reviews.title: The one and Only Tahu Sumedang

reviews.text: Easy place to find. They are opened at both side of the road Balikpapan-Samarinda at around km 50. Cozy place to take a break before continuing your trip. I must say the tahu is one of the best I ever tasted. No so tasty but very tender and creamy. What a food. It served with some kind of sambal made of soy sauce. Unfortunately the other menu is just so so yet still OK, same with the price.
reviews.title: Point to stop...

reviews.text: Their tahu was very similar to original Tahu Sumedang from Sumedang, West Java. Tahu was served fresh from the kitchen. They also served other gorengan such as Gehu (Tahu Isi), Bala-bala (Bakwan Sayur), Combro (Oncom Dijero), and other food such as Soto Bandung, Ayam goreng, etc.
reviews.title: They brought West Java taste to East Kalimantan

reviews.text: The fried tofu is delicious and crunchy. With petis sauce and rawit chili. This place also served many other food and beverages. Suitable as a resting place for a long journey between balikpapan - samarinda
reviews.title: Delicious

reviews.text: If you pass Bukit Suharto, you will pass this "Rumah Makan". Is open 24 hours. The food are Sundanese (West Java) and even the servants are Sundanese as well. This place is good for taking a break after long drive from Samarinda to Balikpapan. The price and the taste are okay.
reviews.title: Sundanese food in Kalimantan

reviews.text:
This place is located midway of Balikpapan and Samarinda.
Always packed with patronage.
The tahu is crispy and tasty, but they did have some runny tofu from time to time. Not so nice.
They have dishes to also fill you up. Try their deep fried burung malon (quail). Very tasty and not chewy.
Next time you're on your way to or from Balikpapan, stop by. :-)
reviews.title: Late lunch

reviews.text:
This is a popular rest stop half way between Samarinda & Balikpapan
Basically it is street food 
Everything is fried however 

But extremely yummy 
Always full

Food is almost cafeteria style 
Order and food is served within a few minutes 

Their most popular item is the silky tofu also known as Tahu 

Which they serve only fried with a local made sauce 

Like a breaded silken tofu which is fried deep

I had the fried noodles with fried egg and fried chicken + yummy home made spicy sauce + fried onion shavings 

Filling 

Then I ordered a whole coconut for the coconut water with ice 

It was yummy!! 
Street food at its best

However this is a large establishment 
At anytime there must be over 100 people who are doing here

High turnaround 
And high capture of traffic from both sides Samarinda + Balikpapan 

A must stop and must visit if you are on this highway
reviews.title: Half Way between Samarinda & Balikpapan

reviews.text: Harga cenderung agak mahal dari warung sejenis, tahu sumedang sama nasi gorengnya rekomended. Bersih
reviews.title: Tahunya joss

reviews.text: Tahunya sih oke, rasa enak harga juga standar. tapi kalau menu lainnya selain tahu kalau pesen siap-siap shock aja pas bayar. intinya kalau di warung tahu belilah tahu aja sama halnya di warung kopi belilah kopi aja ngak usah beli air mineral
reviews.title: tempat untuk istirahat

reviews.text: jalur samarinda hanya bisa ditempuh dari balikpapan ke samarinda melalui jalur darat, ditengah-tengah perjalanan yang bisa sampai 3 jam itu anda bisa menemukan rumah makan tahu sumedang loh di kalimantan
reviews.title: perjalanan bisnis

reviews.text: Kami melakukan perjalanan dinas dari Balikpapan-Samarinda PP. Sekembalinya ke Balikpapan kami mampir di tempat istirahat yang sudah terkenal sejak dahulu di kawasan Hutan Rakyat Bukit Suharto. Kudapan favoritnya adalah Tahu Sumedang, entah bagaimana sejarahnya tahu sumedang bisa sampai ke kawasan yang berada di tengah-tengah antara kota Samarinda dan Balikpapan. Selain tahu sumedang, tersedia juga mie rebus/goreng, dan makanan berat lainnya.
reviews.title: Rehat Sejenak di Tengah Hutan

reviews.text: pengalaman perjalanan yang berkelok kelok dari samarinda balikpapan yang melelahkan terhibur oleh hangatnya tahu sumedang gurih dan enak, lokasinya nyantai
reviews.title: transit sejenak

reviews.text: Perjalanan yang cukup melelahkan, akibat jalan yang berkelok-kelok dan naik-turun, menyebabkan pengemudi dan penumpang perlu berisitirahat, menjelang Bukit  Suharto dari arah Balikpapan, Anda akan menemukan RM Tahu Sumedang di bumi Kalimantan. Tahu Sumedang yang disajikan hangat, mampu melepaskan lelah, sambil menikmati minuman dingin atau hangat.
reviews.title: Tahu Sumedang di Rest Area Balikpapan-Samarinda

reviews.text: Lokasinya berada di pertengahan antara Balikpapan - Samarinda / Tenggarong. Menjadi spot ideal bagi pengendara yang ingin beristirahat sambil mengisi tenaga dengan menu - menu sederhana.
reviews.title: Spot ideal untuk beristirahat dan mengisi perut

reviews.text: Tempat persinggahan yang sangat tepat perjalanan antara Samarinda Balikpapan pp. Dengan Suguhan makanan yang sangat lezat dan cocok di lidah dan di Kantong
reviews.title: Rest Area Balikpapan - Samarinda

reviews.text:
Baru kali ini makan tahu sumedang, lebih enak disini daripada ditempat asalnya... 
Kulitnya renyah dan tahunya uenaaak banget..
Ini very2 recomended
reviews.title: The best tahu...

reviews.text: Cocok untuk istirahan sejenak melepas penat di kendaraan sambil menikmati tahu dan teh hangat sebelum melanjutkan perjalanan (PP) Balikpapan - Samarinda - Kutai
reviews.title: Rest Area 50

reviews.text: Rasanya tidak akan sah apabila sedang dalam perjalanan dari Samarinda ke Balikpapan atau arah sebaliknya, tidak singgah ke Tahu Sumedang. Incaran kami adalah berbagai macam gorengannya yang dijual di food stall tersendiri. Ada tahu sumedang, tahu isi, bakwan, pisang aroma dan lain sebagainya. Semuanya enak-enak, saya sampai kalap mau borong semua. Cocok sekali sebagai kudapan selagi dalam perjalanan.
reviews.title: Wajib singgah demi makan gorengan

reviews.text: Tahunya enak.. Renyah dan berisi padat. Disajikan panas-panas pakai bumbu. Lokasinya pas utk yg sedang perjalanan balikpapan-samarinda
reviews.title: The best tahu I've tasted to date

name: Kedai Kopi Mantaw
address: Jl. Jendral Sudirman no. 101 Pasar Baru, Balikpapan 76113 Indonesia

reviews.text: When you are looking breakfast in balikpapan you can choose this cafe. The best menu is manado porridge, mantau and coffee O. The price is medium. mostly people after fun run, walking in balikpapan street in early morning came to this place to make more enjoying the moment. The problem is difficult parking area when the peak of moment.
reviews.title: The best breakfast with coffee and manado porridge

reviews.text:
The typical of traditional coffee, the aroma is so strong, lil bit bitter yet sweet from the condensed milk.
The mantaw so soft, when its fried, it taste more yummy!

They provide other kind of food, but all I want to try isnthe coffee & the mantaw cos they have good review on them.

1 Siomay dimsum
2 fried mantaw
1 chicken paw
2 coffee
Al only 75k.
reviews.title: Good for brekie.

reviews.text: so many kind of food for breakfast like yellow rice, steam rice, noodle, mantau, dimsum. all of that delicious !!!
reviews.title: good taste for breakfast

reviews.text: Mantaw is the special food and very deliciouS. Coffee milk is very nice composition. So the best coffee milk that i ever drink. Very recomended for breakfast and you can choose any food you like. Very variety food.
reviews.title: Recomended for breakfast

reviews.text: I came to this 'kedai' for dimsum. The taste is quite good and the price is affordable too. Once tried bubur Manado (manadonese porridge) but I didn't recommend it. Nasi tim ayam is served in a big portion and the taste not bad at all...
reviews.title: Cheap dimsum

reviews.text: interesting food (my favorite is nasi kukus & bebek ), bakpaw also is match for breakfast with a coffee
reviews.title: Collaboration Good Coffee and Breakfast Menu

reviews.text: This place is more like a coffee shop or "warung" using local language. It offers lots of variety of food such us: mie pangsit (Steamed noodle with dumplings), nasi campur ( Indonesian mixed Rice), Nasi Kuning ( Yellow rice) and others. for more, it also offers variety of typical Chinese drinks like Soya Been Milk, Chinese liang Tea etc
reviews.title: Variety of Indonesian and Chinese Cuisine

reviews.text: I know, lots of review belong to this restaurant. Suggested as the best place for breakfast but for me turned out it is not. The food is decent, nothing specials. Ordered some noodles, pao (mantau, both steamed and fried), and the main dish. The blackpepper beef as my mantau pairings was disappointed, I expected some chunks of meat but what was served only bite-sizes with overflow broth. We paid as much as mid range restaurants spending with street hawker quality of foods.
reviews.title: Overpriced

reviews.text: Having a regular customer there for the last 3 years.. At least once a week . Provides such a good service and food for those who crave for halal Chinese food
reviews.title: Best place for Porridge

reviews.text: Very good restaurant. Clean and great service. The bubur manado is very good and the fried mantaw is the best in Balikpapan. Good variety of dim sums. Great place for breakfast or lunch.
reviews.title: Best mantaw in Balikpapan

reviews.text: Recomended by local driver to try the fried mantaw (traditional chinese buns steamed/fried) and buy some for take away. Best mantaw i've ever try..
reviews.title: best goldern mantaw

reviews.text: You can already judge from the title how I feel about this place. The dimsum are so good. You should also have iced black coffee or teh tarik. Other favorite dishes are the nasi bakar, bubur manado and nasi hainan. If you want a close parking spot, be there early or else be prepared to park far away or just simply wait till you get one. Also be a little patient when it comes to the service, especially during peak time like Weekend mornings.. nonetheless, I just love the old chinese coffee shop atmosphere it has.
reviews.title: Fave Breakfast Joint

reviews.text: I read that it was a good place to have breakfast, but i was so disappointed. i ordered mie ayam pangsit (chicken noodle with dumpling) and my husband ordered bubur ayam (chicken porridge). it tasted flat. the chicken noodle was not savory as I expected as always I eat chicken noodle in java. It's lack of broth taste. the dumpling skin was raw and hard to chew, and tasteless. the dumpling only contented of flour skin and almost no filling. the chicken porridge lack of chicken itself. Bandung chicken porridge is way better than this. the siomay was too sticky and tasteless. actually i like chinese food because of its rich taste. but this was under my expectation.sorry. i hope you can improve the taste of your foods.thanks
reviews.title: it's under expectation

reviews.text:
don't know why this kopitiam style eatery becomes popular breakfast spot. yes they served varieties of foods and drinks (you can see the menu almost everywhere in the wall). but you can find it elsewhere too.  
yes it's crowded inside, but doesn't mean this is the best one. only hype, perhaps.
reviews.title: not that impressive place (or foods)

reviews.text: This is one of my favorite place to have breakfast and lunch. There are many kinds of food you can order, from yellow rice, porridge, manado porridge, dimsum, hainanese chicken and so on. Try their teh susu (milk tea), is the best in town.
reviews.title: One of the best breakfast spot

reviews.text:
like the food .. the traditional cake and most of it yummy Nasi Tim Ayam .. and its cheap 
visit there every weekend with family and friends
reviews.title: breakfeast spot

reviews.text:
It's a heaven for people who likes breakfast time.
This traditional restaurant open since early morning around 6 am until afternoon usually at 3 or 4 depends on the customer. This restaurant provides many types of cantonese breakfast you would want. From various mantao, bakpao, noodles, traditional drinks, chips, poridge, steamed rice, finger food. I can't get enough of their food, it's all delicious!
reviews.title: Great local restaurant for breakfast lover in Balikpapan

reviews.text:
dulu pernah makan disini sekali, enak2 saja.
kemudian hari ini makan kedua kali nya pesan melalui gofood nasi kuning.
dan setelah sy makan 1/4 porsi nya sy menemukan ini (digambar).
sy kurang tau itu serangga apa dan sy ngga berani melihat nya lebih detail, karena (maaf) jijik.
reviews.title: Ketemu sesuatu di nasi kuning nya. Entah apa, dilihat sendiri sj

reviews.text:
Makanannya enak.
Waktu mampir aku cobain cakwe, fish dimsum, roti bakar srikaya, bubur manado dan kopi susu.
Pilihan menunya banyak. Bahkan ada jualan kue basah.
Pokoknya wajib mampir kalo ke Balikpapan.
reviews.title:
Makanannya enak.
Waktu mampir

reviews.text:
Tempat sarapan ini populer, pengunjungnya ramai. Lokasinya di ruko tak jauh dari depot Miki yang populer juga.
Rumah makan ini menjual berbagai jenis makanan, termasuk dim sum, dan bahkan bubur manado.
Sesuai dengan namanya, mantaw di sini adalah salah satu makanan andalannya, rasanya tidak mengecewakan. Rasa mantaw gorengnya enak. Mantaw kukusnya belum mencoba. Bakpao kacang hijaunya lumayan. Tahwanya agak kasar, kurang lembut, tapi mungkin ada yang lebih suka teksturnya yang begini. Kuahnya manis dan rasa jahenya cukup kuat, sayang agak pahit rasa jahenya. 
Kopi hitamnya mempunyai rasa keasaman yang cukup kuat.
reviews.title: Mantaw yang enak di tempat sarapan yang populer

name: Warung Tulung Agung
address: Jl. Jendral Sudirman 70, Balikpapan 76112 Indonesia

reviews.text:
They claim they're experts on Rawon and Pecel. O only try the Rawon. It was not disappointing. The meat was tender. The Rawon's soups was delicious.

I also try the salty egg. It was too tender. As if it was not properly cooked. Maybe I'm just not in luck.

Next visit I'll try the Pecel.

The only major issue was the parking lot.
reviews.title: Affordable tasty food

reviews.text:
Almost all restaurants in Sepinggan Airport are expensive. If you want to get cheap food for lunch, just get outside and walk for about 500meters away to the three junction. You will find restaurant that won't make any dent on your wallet.
This place is famous for its Nasi Pecel and Nasi Rawon. But I've eaten these foods so many times in Java. So I tried other menus, Nasi Oseng Papaya's leave, Oseng Usus and some Kerupuk. For baverage, I chose Orange Juice. It all cost 35k IDR.
reviews.title: Perfect spot for having cheap lunch when arriving at Sepinggan Airport

reviews.text: If you miss authentic east javanese Nasi pecel while in Balikpapan, then you should visit this warung. You can request any topping you like, including peyek teri. For very reasonable cheap price. And the portion itself is huge. Aplenty for a person with big appetite. Just try it!
reviews.title: Best Pecel in town

reviews.text:
I heard about this warung through some local friends. Clean, cheap and excellent food! The Nasi Pecel is probably the best I ever tasted. The Nasi Rawon is also good.
Highly recommended!
reviews.title: Great Nasi Pecel!!!

reviews.text:
I know this place from my friend. He asked me to get lunch here. He said it is the best nasi pecel in town!

I order nasi pecel with chicken breast. And when it touch my tongue, the taste was great and have big portion! it was lilttle hard to fins this place. But it was worth!
reviews.title: Rich taste!

reviews.text: Boiled mix vegetable serve with peanut sauce, crackers and steam rice (read : nasi pecel), this one of the best traditional culinary form javanese, but you can found this food in Balikpapan city, the place near with Bank Danamon Bali, this area called Pasar Baru, you can enjoy Nasi Pecel with variants topping..servce with fried chicken, cow pulmonary, and you can found others traditional food likes rawon, and soto. This place very recommended , and you must try.
reviews.title: Never ending story ...Nasi Pecel

reviews.text:
The infamous javanese resto in Balikpapan.
Must try for rawon and pecel tulungagung.
Though, it is quite tricky to find the restaurant.
reviews.title: Exotic Javanese Cuisine

reviews.text: Warung Klasik dengan menu utama Pecel, tetapi sekarang banyak variannya. namun begitu pecel tetap menjadi menu favorit
reviews.title: The Legend Pecel Bahari

reviews.text: nasi pecel yang nikmat, bumbu kacangnya lembut dan juga tidak terlalu kasar dengan selera peda yang bisa disesuaikan dengan keinginan kita.
reviews.title: nasi pecel dengan bumbu kacang yang lembut

reviews.text: Warungnya cukup nyaman serta layanannya baik dan ramah. Menu andalan Nasi pecel selain itu tersedia Rawon, Soto, Nasi campur, Kare ayam dan lainnya. Nasi pecel isinya cukup lengkap dengan bumbu yang nikmat, ditambah daging empal yang rasanya gurih serta dagingnya empuk. Rawon rasanya segar dan nikmat dengan dagingnya yang empuk serta sambalnya mantap.
reviews.title: Pecel Nikmat

reviews.text: Warung ini boleh dibilang sederhana tampilannya. Memiliki 2 lantai yang selalu penuh terisi pelanggan pada saat jam makan siang membangkitkan rasa penasaran saya. Pada kunjungan pertama, saya memilih menu khas mereka, nasi pecel dengan tambahan lauk empal daging. Ternyata memang rasanya juara, bumbu pecel yang pas rasanya dan sayurannya juga segar. Pada kesempatan lain saya mencoba rawon yang juga tidak kalah lezatnya.
reviews.title: Pecel dan Rawonnya Juara

reviews.text: Pilihan makanan ada sejak makan siang, nasi campur, soto dan rawon ada disini. termasuk enak, dan harga juga murah.
reviews.title: Nasi pecelnya ok lah.

reviews.text: Harga standart makanan di Balikpapan , rasanya luar biasa enak dgn porsi yg pas dan lokasi yang mudah dijangkau
reviews.title: Nasi pecel Ayam

reviews.text: Depot yang sudah lama ini tetap rasannya. Rawon enak, pecel enak, ayam kare juga enak... enak deh untuk makan siang oke. Kurangnya cuman parkirannya. Tapi pelayanan yg cepat jadi orang yg lapar juga langsung di layani. Walau pun sempit worth it lah. Langanan lama sih
reviews.title: Depot enak dan cepat penyajiannya

reviews.text: Warungnya biasa aja karena ruko & terletak di seberang pasar baru. Ga terlihat menarik dari penampilannya. Tapi jgn salah yg makan ruamee banget! Disini nasi pecelnya bisa milih antara pake ayam, empal, lele atau telur. Bumbu pecelnya nendang banget ditambah rempeyek n krupuknya yg greget. 1 porsi 25rb untuk pecel ini...
reviews.title: Pecel termanteb se balikpapan!

reviews.text: Sy nyoba daging sapi bumbu, sayur pepaya gak pake pait, usus Dan peyek.. Hr berikutnya ikan bandeng dan pare. Semuanya cocok dilidah saya.. Bumbunya pas.. G keasinan, g hambar. Enakla byk menu pilihan Yg laennya
reviews.title: Menu prasmanan

reviews.text: Selama saya tinggal di Balikpapan ga nemu pecel seenak di Warung Tulung Agung. Menurut sejarah warung ini sudah ada sejak Balikpapan mulai bertumbuh. Jadi orang Balikpapan sudah tidak asing lagi. Menunya adalah menu umum yang ada di pulau jawa. Namun bagi orang2 perantauan menu ini menjadi lebih spesial karena bisa mengobati rasa kangen kampung halaman.
reviews.title: Pecelnya Joss

reviews.text: Menurut saya pribadi sebagai pencinta nasi pecel, nasi pecel yang disajikan di sini tidak istimewa. Kuahnya cenderung hambar hanya menonjolkan rasa pedas, dan daging ayamnya tidak cukup empuk untuk dinikmati. Ruangannya kecil, panas, selalu saja ada pengamen, dan pelayanan yang lama cukup bagi saya untuk tidak akan kembali ke tempat ini.
reviews.title: Pelayanan Lambat, Panas, dan Rasanya Biasa Saja

reviews.text: Menu andalannya adalah Pecel dengan lauk pilihan seperti ayam, empal daging ataupun udang goring. Bumbu pecelnya enak banget plus ditambah peyek kriuknya yummy., Rawonnya juga enak, bener-bener kental dan berasa klueknya... you should try this one !!
reviews.title: Alternatif for Quick Lunch

reviews.text: Rumah makan ini selalu ramai, apalagi di jam makan siang. Tapi mengantri pun tak masalah,  karna menu makanan yang disediakan disini sangat layak untuk ditunggu. Favorit saya adalah nasi pecel dengan daging empal. Masalah rasa jangan ditanya,sangat sedap. Porsinya pun terbilang dan dijamin puas. Ini satu2 nya tempat yang saya datangi ketika rindu masakan kampung halaman "TulungAgung".
reviews.title: Makanan Jawa terbaik di Balikpapan

name: Marugame Udon
address: Jl. Jendral Sudirman no. 1 Balikpapan Plaza Lantai Dasar, Balikpapan 76114 Indonesia

reviews.text: MU always be my family & friend's favourite. But we have to queue if we want to eat. MU at Balikpapan maybe 1 of any MU outlet that we don't have queue. About the taste? Never doubt it
reviews.title: MU tanpa ngantri? Ke Bpn ajah

reviews.text: Been in Osaka branch. Very tasty udon. Reasonably priced. Becoming one of the popular options for japanese restaurants in Indonesia. Self service. We just go through the line and order. Then you pay at the end of the line. Simple and quick . Yet the taste is good. Try the Kamaage Udon that comes in the traditional  wooden bowl. They even have the family size. The tempura and chicken katsu are also delicious. Order ocha or lipton tea for refill as many as you want. The udon is freshly made.
reviews.title: Tasty Japanese Udon

reviews.text:
I am just happy since knew that this restaurant available in my city. Same taste with muragame udon at the other place. 
Good standard.
reviews.title: Saya Suka

reviews.text:
I ate it on my lunch time, nice taste and coxy restaurant, very easy to find the place. suit for Indonesian who like to have big portion on every eating time heheehee, big noodle portion made me over full, it costed average IDR.48.000 ++

Fast service and well equipped, recommended place
reviews.title: Nice Udon in Mall

reviews.text: I normally go to Marugame Udon with my daughters because they love noodles. You pick up a tray, order your noodles, grab some tempura, pay and sit on a table. Really fast! My favorite is the Niku Udon. The shrimp tempura is also pretty good. There's free flow of cold ocha tea. The prices are very affordable and the food recommended.
reviews.title: Real fast and good food!

reviews.text:
They has best udon in town. No kidding. Haha...
If you are in the mall and need hot serve food, you should try this one.
The has very crunchy tempura and best noodle on their udon.
The variety of the food is not much, only some udon, rice and tempura but it's okay.
The place is really has japanese ambience and they also have real ocha. If you love japanese food, you should try eat here.
reviews.title: Great japanese food taste

reviews.text:
When I was confused about what to eat at Balikpapan Plaza, decided to try this restaurant.
Taste good. The decorations also good. I'd love to come here again.
reviews.title: Good food. Good ambience.

reviews.text:
Had my lunch at the Marugame Udon at Plaza Balikpapan while I was on a business trip.
In comparison to the Marugame Udon in Surabaya, the menu option was not much.
But I'll give the restaurant's ambience a plus, because the place was comfortable.
reviews.title: Not much food option, good ambience

reviews.text: Just opened less than a year, but this place has become favorite. Not so many option, but what they serve is very good, so delicious. The service is quick and nice. The place is also relaxing. Worth with what to spent.
reviews.title: So delicious

reviews.text: Tempuranya enak, minuman bisa di refill, saya suka menu nasi daripada udon, tapi rata-rata makanan yang disajikan enak dan cocok untuk makan keluarga
reviews.title: Suka banget

reviews.text: rumah makan yang didominasi masakan jepang seperti ramen dan udon atau mie yang besar. rasa sukiyaki nya menurut saya terlalu manis.
reviews.title: sukiyaki yang terlalu manis

reviews.text: Saya kira inilah satu-satunya rumah makan yang menyediakan udon di Balikpapan. Sebagai rumah makan waralaba yang sudah banyak memiliki gerai di Indonesia, Marugame Udon cukup menghilangkan rasa rindu kepada makanan Udon dan Tempura bila sedang berada di Balikpapan. Rasanya ok, tempatnya ok, layanan juga ok.
reviews.title: Aneka Udon dan Tempura Yang Menggoda

reviews.text: Niku Udon menjadi pilihan saya kali ini. Udon disajikan dengan sup kake dashi dan daging sapi sukiyaki yang manis juga gurih. Tekstur udon kenyal dan lembut. Kuah terasa segar, manis dan gurih. Yummy.
reviews.title: udon sungguh enak lezat

reviews.text:
first time nyoba udon dan enak hehe side dish aka bala2 aka gorengan juga cucok :p 
staff ramah dan suasananya jg oke, pas pokoknya
reviews.title: first time

reviews.text: Interior restorannya oke, pelayanan stafnya ramah. Di bagian depan pengunjung bisa melihat proses pembuatan mie udonnya dari tepungnya yg khas. Saya coba Kitsune Udon, mie udonnya emang enak banget loh. Harga makanan di restoran ini juga cukup terjangkau. Free refill ice lemon tea dan green tea pula. Saya puas makan di restoran ini
reviews.title: Mie Udon dan Tempura yang Istimewa

photos.caption: Kitsune Udon di Restoran Marugame Udon

reviews.text:
rasanya sangat khas seperti Udon di Jepang. Mie nya halus dan kuahnya berasa banget. lalu untuk cabai, kecap asin dan lainnya dapat ambil sendiri suka suka kita.
free ocha flow juga
reviews.title: Best Udon in Town

reviews.text: Saya makan malam disini dengan mantap. Memilih beef udon sebagai menu utama dan ebi tempura sebagai menu tambahan. Merupakan restoran cepat saja dengan metode nampan berjalan. Jadi di depan kami memesan, disiapkan,  tambah menu lainnya, minuman dan membayar. Makan malam disini cukup mantap. Udon yang padat dan banyak, topping daging yang banyak dan lembut dan ebi furai yang lembut dengan saus yang gurih. Malam malam mantap.
reviews.title: Makan malam mantap

reviews.text: Margumenyaaa enak bangeett.. Waitresnya helpful bgt.. Lokasinya yg ada di Plaza Balikpapan strategis banget. Recommended place
reviews.title: Itadakimsu  enak banget

reviews.text:
Kunjungan yg pertama kesini setelah diajak istri,aslinya ga suka makanan japanese,tp setelah mencoba taste ny cocok di lidah,harga bersahabat..
Yang saya suka,waitress nya pada berjilbab semua,depan resto terpampang label halal MUI jd tdk perlu kawatir.lokasinya di pelataran depan pintu belakang mall
Minusnya tempat nya kurang dingin
reviews.title: Konsep japanese food yang islami

reviews.text:
Paling cukup suka dengan udon yang ada di Marugame Udon, ke-khawatiran saya akan adanya perbedaan rasa dengan di cabang-cabang Marugame Udon dikota lain karena di Balikpapan merupakan tempat makan yang baru buka dengan tidak terbukti karena rasanya tetap sama hahaha.
Tempatnya selalu sangat ramai, mungkin karena masih euphoria tempat makan baru di Balikpapan. Secara design interior dan eksterior dari tempat ini sama saja dengan di cabang-cabang Marugame Udon lainnya di kota-kota lain. Namun nilai lebihnya tempatnya cukup luas, karena ada Marugame di kota lain yang tempatnya lenih kecil.
reviews.title: Akhirnya Marugame Udon, ada di Balikpapan.

name: Batakan Beach Cafe
address: Jln. Mulawarman 03, Balikpapan 76115 Indonesia

reviews.text: This is one of the best place I had visited.  The cafe needs to have some upgrading but the view is so great and the food is nice. Staff is friendly. I had the best drinks there and the nacho chips were great. There are lots of parking space in this cafe.
reviews.title: Best view and clean beach Cafe

reviews.text:
Nice spot on the beach, this restaurant offers a good price/quality courses. The variety of dishes is wide and goes from all the western meat and local dishes.

Happy hour every day from 1800 to 2100 make this place one of the cheapest of BPN.
reviews.title: Various dishes (local and western)

reviews.text:
Great service from the staff. Highly recommended by many ex-pats over here as a clean & safe place to eat.

Been here a few times this week and by the third visit they remembered my drink and seating preferences.
reviews.title: nice place!

reviews.text:
The pasta was very average.
We ordered some western food It was a very poor presentation tough the flavors were not horrible.
reviews.title: very average

reviews.text: We are frequent visitors to this restaurant and are always happy but just wanted to add my husband & I had Sirloin Steaks on Saturday night and we both agreed it was the best steak we had tasted since our arrival in Indonesia over a year ago.  Well done to BBC .
reviews.title: Steak

reviews.text: My husband and I come to BBC very frequently as it is close to where we live in Balikpapan. The food is always good - especially the Mexican fajitas and burgers - and the service is great for Balikpapan. They have a good happy hour (2 for 1 beers, 3 for 2 cocktails.not sure of the exact times though) and the cocktails are delicious! If you live in Balikpapan, they offer free delivery of meals, which is generally quick and the meals are still hot. The decor both inside and outside the restaurant is a little bit dated, but it's a great choice for lunch or a casual dinner.
reviews.title: Great Food and Service!

reviews.text: As titled said, ample parking lot are provided and local transportation such as angkot can be found easily. Plenty of restaurant, by the beach as your selection. Overall it's a good place for relaxing.
reviews.title: Great place if you want some fresh air

reviews.text: Good service and food is consistent standard. Not fine dining but quite okay. Their fajitas's are quite good and beers are cold. A populart place for lunch during the work day. Has a very nice beach outlook and the sea breeze can be quite pleasant in the afternoon.
reviews.title: Good for lunch on a work day

reviews.text: There's been some mistake in this review and photo. Batakan Beach Club (BBC) is different from Beach House( in here they call it Batakan Beach House). They are only 3miles away from each other. Batakan beach Club or BBC is a fine dining restaurant. The photo shows wood table and chair with bar and billiard table(pool). Flags from country around the world is hung around the bar. The food is very recomended with great service. The interior looks very masculin. Lots of expats dine here for lunch n dinner. The view out side the resto is average. You only can look at the plain sea with no tree or coral sand! You even cannot reach the sea because it is closed with bar fence. ( find Beach House to see my review about it)
reviews.title: Masculin style

reviews.text: I have eaten here most nights this month. They have very friendly staff, cold beer and a large menu with great food. Saturdays there is a BBQ.
reviews.title: Good food

reviews.text:
I've been here arround 4months ago but it was so Gorgeous! 
saya berasal dari kota ini walaupun sudah lama stay di Bali tapi Balikpapan ternyata juga sangat sangat nice for dinner or enjoy beaches dengan nice konsep Guest house nya, n good music too.
smoga akan lebh banyak tempat2 seperti ini lagi..
Trust me that I will cme to this place when im back to home for sure !

cheers!
reviews.title: Gorgeous, Romantic n Nice food

reviews.text: Good venue, great food, cold beer, many old expats sitting around whinging about Indo, but great for a story or two. Outside area will be brilliant when finished..!!! Just remember to keep your taxi or driver with you when you get there as if you let them leave you could be waiting for literally hours to get another..!!
reviews.title: Great Location

reviews.text: its a nice place to have a simple meal.  pool table is available at no extra cost. i am a vegetarian. the chef managed to fix up spaghetti with few veggies in tomato sauce, with tomato soup on the side.  appreciated :)
reviews.title: decent place.

reviews.text:
I went to this restaurant for lunch with friends. Nice place but we have to wait for long time for our orders.

I choose Salmon Medallion, the fries and veggies were great but the sauce is not a good combination with the salmon
reviews.title: good food, slow service

reviews.text: I think now the chef in BBC already change coz the taste of a food different as I used to taste before.
reviews.title: the food taste diffrent

reviews.text:
There are only two places in Balikpapan that I personally consider had a decent western/mexican food, and Batakan Beach Club is one of them (the other one is Lila's place, formerly known as Jack's Place also located at Batakan area, best burger in town, period)
This place has a nice ambience, not too crowded, great for hanging out with friends, or romantic dinner, very nice food for this li'l town, decent steak, and perfectly-chilled beer, mind you I'm very picky about my beer temperature :)
reviews.title: Good Food and Ambience

reviews.text:
Went there with couple friends to grab out some lunch. During working days it normally packed with expatriates who works in the offices along the area [mainly service related for mining or oilfield]
I ordered some beef nachos and it was good. My friend ordered Chinese food "sapo tahu" and it was a bit disappointing.. the veggies and the tofu were too soggy and it tastes bland.
Because the segment for food and price are mainly for expatriates so the price is maybe a tad bit too pricey for some Indonesian.
The plus side is the scenery of the beach, although it's not a nice beach as beaches in Bali but still it's nice view :)

I have a few bad experiences at this place. The bar staff and manager are really rude and unhelpful. The barman put lots of extra drinks on our bill and we were forced to pay for them. The food was terrible and one of my friends got food poisoning. Stay away from this place it is a dump.
reviews.title: DON'T go to BBC

reviews.text:
Due to far from town and expensive, eventhoug it is cozy it is more expartriate compare to local. I think it is because the area.
Food taste match to foreginer rather than local
reviews.title: BBC

reviews.text: food just okay, but the scenery of beach and ambiance are nice
reviews.title: Good scenery

name: Kaizeki Japanese Restaurant
address: Jl. Letjen Suprapto no. 1 Blue Sky Hotel, Balikpapan 76131 Indonesia

reviews.text: The teppanyaki is the most favourable food when I visitee the restaurant. The beef and vegetable are so fresh and good ambience as well. The staff is really nice and friendly
reviews.title: Good food

reviews.text: Went to this restaurant for special moments. The food is average in my opinion. Pricing is also expensive compare it with the taste. The staff is less friendly, they are not showing a smiley face that suppose to make customer feel comfortable. And the chef is not even greeting us. He is cooking in a rush, no attraction (teppanyaki identity) like advertised or said in other reviews. Again, no smiley face from the chef. A very standard thing in restaurant, especialy when it is located @ 4 stars hotel. I am dissapointed & definitely would not come back with this kind of service. My review is based on my experience & they are not te be generalized. But if you want to give it a try just once, go ahead & write down your review.
reviews.title: Average

owner_response.text:
Dear ttt4android,

Greetings from Blue Sky Hotel Balikpapan..

I sincerely appreciate you taking the time to give us your feedback. It is with sincere regret that I note your dissatisfaction with our service and facilities.
Rest assured that we have taken serious note of your comments and we will strengthen our focus on our training in these specific areas.

I hope this experience will not alter your confidence in Restaurant and Hotel Blue Sky Balikpapan and that you will give us the opportunity of welcoming you again.

We are thank you for your attention and understanding.

Regards,
Renny Margaretha
Public Relations Manager

reviews.text: Great Japanese food and BBQ alot to choose from, Staff are very helpful a good selection of drinks you will enjoy.
reviews.title: Very nice food and great cooks

owner_response.text:
Dear couta2160,

Thank you for posting your review on TripAdvisor following your recent visit to  Kaizeki Japanese Restaurant. We are thrilled to read that you had a great dining experience and enjoyed the service provided by our team members. 

Once again, thank you for the rating and we look forward to welcoming you back

Assistant F&B Manager
